# 1d87c78d0f134c44b1016767b473ad43
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:216
msgid "Administration Tools"
msgstr ""

# edf815074a214302a5fede3f83e03902
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:218
msgid "Traffic Server offers the following administration options:"
msgstr ""

# cd1744abbcb3415096fa2082a013285b
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:220
msgid ""
"The :program:`traffic_ctl` command-line interface is a text-based "
"interface from which you can monitor Traffic Server performance and "
"network traffic, as well as configure the Traffic Server system. From "
"Traffic Line, you can execute individual commands or script a series of "
"commands in a shell."
msgstr ""

# 28c7103a993748a488ddad8210c5ed23
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:226
msgid ""
"Various configuration files enable you to configure Traffic Server "
"through a simple file-editing and signal-handling interface. Any changes "
"you make through Traffic Line is automatically made to the configuration "
"files as well."
msgstr ""

# ff35b553a56a416e9e9680af841fe747
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:231
msgid ""
"Finally, there is a clean C API which can be put to good use from a "
"multitude of languages. The Traffic Server Admin Client demonstrates this"
" for Perl."
msgstr ""

# c336fa394e274f6f8f76d08aa124051e
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:236
msgid "Traffic Analysis Options"
msgstr ""

# 057a3c531b7040d0975790535c01b69b
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:238
msgid ""
"Traffic Server provides several options for network traffic analysis and "
"monitoring:"
msgstr ""

# 8d43460982114598acc96ab998c49920
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:241
msgid ""
":program:`traffic_ctl` enables you to collect and process statistics "
"obtained from network traffic information."
msgstr ""

# 0e0219eafcd14c07ad16573bee5caa47
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:244
msgid ""
"Transaction logging enables you to record information (in a log file) "
"about every request Traffic Server receives and every error it detects. "
"By analyzing the log files, you can determine how many clients used the "
"Traffic Server cache, how much information each of them requested, and "
"what pages were most popular. You can also see why a particular "
"transaction was in error and what state the Traffic Server was in at a "
"particular time. For example, you can see that Traffic Server was "
"restarted or that cluster communication timed out."
msgstr ""

# 4d66bc7cd14549918bb9a8180658887f
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:253
msgid ""
"Traffic Server supports several standard log file formats, such as Squid "
"and Netscape, and its own custom format. You can analyze the standard "
"format log files with off-the-shelf analysis packages. To help with log "
"file analysis, you can separate log files so that they contain "
"information specific to protocol or hosts."
msgstr ""

# 72161568a8c04c089205cac6ec9ec9be
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:259
msgid ""
"Traffic analysis options are described in more detail in :ref"
":`monitoring-traffic`."
msgstr ""

# 396d9c205a4e453a8f8ec1f2557abd10
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:261
msgid ""
"Traffic Server logging options are described in :ref:`working-with-log-"
"files`."
msgstr ""

# 8b0996bdb42d44d2bd16ca36b74aa98c
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:264
msgid "Traffic Server Security Options"
msgstr ""

# 0f4a7fd5ce3b4f06a45ceaefb46cba17
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:266
msgid ""
"Traffic Server provides numerous options that enable you to establish "
"secure communication between the Traffic Server system and other "
"computers on the network. Using the security options, you can do the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

# a5a264df3ec24b4aad24c325eb59741b
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:271
msgid "Control client access to the Traffic Server proxy cache."
msgstr ""

# 4100feeacad742e4a90afb3ca0a7beee
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:273
msgid ""
"Configure Traffic Server to use multiple DNS servers to match your site's"
" security configuration. For example, Traffic Server can use different "
"DNS servers, depending on whether it needs to resolve hostnames located "
"inside or outside a firewall. This enables you to keep your internal "
"network configuration secure while continuing to provide transparent "
"access to external sites on the Internet."
msgstr ""

# fc969081b21b40f4b16e2375490d47f0
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:280
msgid ""
"Configure Traffic Server to verify that clients are authenticated before "
"they can access content from the Traffic Server cache."
msgstr ""

# 01f841a4234d4438abdf3084feb767d3
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:283
msgid ""
"Secure connections in reverse proxy mode between a client and Traffic "
"Server, and Traffic Server and the origin server, using the SSL "
"termination option."
msgstr ""

# 17c3529eae374be58e38941f79efa424
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:287
msgid "Control access via SSL (Secure Sockets Layer)."
msgstr ""

# 386cd1424ae04466875119f30d9925e0
#: ../../admin-guide/introduction.en.rst:289
msgid ""
"Traffic Server security options are described in more detail in :ref"
":`admin-security`."
msgstr ""

